The paper presents a novel cost function for semi-supervised learning of neural networks that encourages compact clustering of the latent space to facilitate separation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of graph-based regularization and label propagation, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also evaluates its approach on three benchmarks, which suggests that it could belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
